android.car.app

类 ControlledRemoteCarTaskView

  • java.lang.Object
    • SurfaceView
      • android.car.app.RemoteCarTaskView
        • android.car.app.ControlledRemoteCarTaskView

  • public final class ControlledRemoteCarTaskView
extends RemoteCarTaskView
    A ControlledRemoteCarTaskView should be used when the launch intent of the task is known before hand. The underlying task will be restarted if it is crashed depending on the autoRestartOnCrash.

    It should be preferred when:

    • The underlying task is meant to be started by the host and be there forever.

      • addInsets

        public void addInsets(int index,
                      int type,
                      Rect frame)
        从类复制的说明: RemoteCarTaskView
        Adds the given insets on the Task. The given frame for the insets type are applied to the underlying task right away. If a rectangle for an insets type was added previously, it will be replaced with the new value. If a rectangle for a insets type was already added, but is not specified currently in insets, it will remain applied to the task. Clients should explicitly call RemoteCarTaskView.removeInsets(int, int) to remove the rectangle for that insets type from the underlying task.
        覆盖:
        addInsets 在类中 RemoteCarTaskView
        参数:
        index - An owner might add multiple insets sources with the same type. This identifies them.
        type - The insets type of the insets source.
        frame - The rectangle area of the insets source.

      • removeInsets

        public void removeInsets(int index,
                         int type)
        从类复制的说明: RemoteCarTaskView
        Removes the given insets from the Task. Note: This will only remove the insets that were added using RemoteCarTaskView.addInsets(int, int, Rect)
        覆盖:
        removeInsets 在类中 RemoteCarTaskView
        参数:
        index - An owner might add multiple insets sources with the same type. This identifies them.
        type - The insets type of the insets source. This doesn't accept the composite types.
